    "Note how the reward function employed will vary depending on the variables to be considered in the problem.",
    "As discussed later, the details of this function is one of the main design decisions in DRL.",
    "Finally, the actions to be performed by the agent will depend on the problem we are facing with.",
    "For example, in problems where the actions consist of adjusting the heating and cooling setpoints of the HVAC system, the action space may be discrete-there is a finite number of actions where each action is a tuple with fixed setpoint values, or continuous-each setpoint is a real number to be adjusted.",
